Ansible architecture — control node, managed nodes, inventory

Ansible is an open-source IT automation engine used for configuration management, application deployment, cloud provisioning, and 
orchestration. Maintained by Red Hat and written in Python, it allows teams to manage infrastructure as code (IaC). Instead of executing 
manual terminal commands on individual systems, administrators write human-readable blueprints that enforce a desired system state 
automatically across thousands of machines.

Ansible works using push based mechanism. Chef is pull based mechanism - It pulls configuration of all the servers and then updates 
accordingly.

